<% title 'Regional Chapters' %>
<% description "Developers Connect Philippines (DevCon) is a non-proﬁt organization which aims to promote the \"IT Pinoy Talent\" mainly by providing a unique venue for IT students, educators, professionals and enthusiasts to Sync, Support and Succeed." %>
<% set_meta_tags :open_graph => {
  :title => "#{ENV['title']} | Regional Chapters",
  :description => "Developers Connect Philippines (DevCon) is a non-proﬁt organization which aims to promote the \"IT Pinoy Talent\" mainly by providing a unique venue for IT students, educators, professionals and enthusiasts to Sync, Support and Succeed.",
  :type  => :website,
  :url   => chapters_url,
  :image => [opengraph_thumb_url, { :width => 200, :height => 200 }]
}, :image_src => opengraph_thumb_url %>
<div class="row faq">
  <div class="col-sm-9">
    <h1>Regional Chapters</h1>

    <div class="row" id="devcon-chapters">
      <div class="col-sm-12">
        <p>Being a fast growing community, DevCon already has local chapters in <strong>Cebu</strong>, <strong>Davao</strong>, <strong>Cagayan de Oro (CDO)</strong>, <strong>Iloilo</strong>, and <strong>Bacolod</strong>. Each chapter has its own set of events and a steering committee. Here are the current chapter heads:</p>
        <div class="row officer">
          <div class="col-sm-12 profile">
            <h3><span class="caps">Val Enriquez</span>, DevCon Bai! (Cebu) Chapter Head</h3>
            <p class="twitter-handle"><a href="http://twitter.com/valian112" target="_blank">@valian112</a></p>
            <p><%= image_tag "faq/val.jpg", :alt => "Val", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> Val is a Software Engineer at Exist Software Labs, Inc. Graduated at University of Cebu - Banilad Campus with a Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology. He loves playing deduction games on his free time. He just goes with the flow in terms of learning new technologies and likes to share some ideas by organizing brief code camps with the help of his colleagues and friends in the industry who are really passionate on what they do.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row officer">
          <div class="col-sm-12 profile">
            <h3><span class="caps">Cris John Tagupa</span>, DevCon Cagayan de Oro Chapter Head</h3>
            <p class="twitter-handle"><a href="https://twitter.com/cjtagupa" target="_blank">@cjtagupa</a></p>
            <p><%= image_tag "faq/devcon-cris.jpg", :alt => "Cris", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> Cris is a Web Developer at Force12 Media, Inc. He holds a Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, graduating Magna cum Laude from Liceo de Cagayan University. He considers himself as very lucky to be able to work on something that he loves so much. Code is Poetry.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row officer">
          <div class="col-sm-12 profile">
            <h3><span class="caps">Jaymar Somosot</span>, DevCon Davao Chapter Head</h3>
            <p class="twitter-handle"><a href="http://twitter.com/strangershots" target="_blank">@strangershots</a></p>
            <p><%= image_tag "faq/js.jpg", :alt => "Jay", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> Jay is an autodidact who was introduced to DevCon in 2011 and has been a passionate volunteer since. His interest is on Open Source technology, DevOps, Cloud Computing and other SysAdmin related stuffs. He is also currently one of the community lead for DALIUS (Davao Linux User) Group that promotes the use and support of the Linux Operating System, and Free/Libre,Open Source Software.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row officer">
          <div class="col-sm-12 profile">
            <h3><span class="caps">Jingo Rodriguez</span>, DevCon Iloilo Chapter Head</h3>
            <p class="twitter-handle"><a href="http://twitter.com/JingoRodriguez" target="_blank">@JingoRodriguez</a></p>
            <p><%= image_tag "faq/jingo.jpg", :alt => "Jingo", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> Jingo is currently a web developer at Voiceless Technologies, a nocturnal coder and loves to code a lot, also has worked with mobile and game development companies. He is interested with open source and cloud computing technologies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row officer">
          <div class="col-sm-12 profile">
            <h3><span class="caps">Edwin Salinas</span>, DevCon Bacolod Chapter Head</h3>
            <p class="twitter-handle" style="font-size:7px">&nbsp;</p>
            <p><%= image_tag "faq/ed.jpg", :alt => "Ed", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> Ed graduated from FEU Institute of Technology (FIT) with a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science. He worked with software companies and as a part-time computer science professor at FIT when he was still in Manila. He is interested in startups, software development, and information security.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="apply-local-chapter">To apply for a local chapter, feel free to email our Executive Director via <a href="mailto:anthea@devcon.ph">anthea@devcon.ph</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

